spans.text: The path that flings across the reedy plain
that flings across the reedy plain
in her green dress , nature never roves
in her green dress , nature never roves
no melting clouds refresh the groves
that the wages of the day allow A social blaze to cheer their evening hearth
laughs the jovial voice of mirth
the chaste housewife , with maternal care , Her thrifty distaff plies , in grave attire ; Blessed to behold her ruddy offspring wear The full resemblance of their sturdy fire
such coarse fare their homely board As fits the genius of their little fate , Free from those ills that haunt their pampered lord
the storms that strike the land With wild dismay roll harmless over their head
the load of weary life to
breathe heaven's pure and cheerful air , To be but living tenants of the grave
The reverend comeliness of green old age
They still through life with pleased attention ply
that learning's but ingenious pain , Might hail their happier lot , and sighing say , " O had I thus , within the dark profound , " By daily labour earned my daily food
O had I thus , within the dark profound , " By daily labour earned my daily food
I thus , within the dark profound , " By daily labour earned my daily food
an anxious wish , or pang of heart , " That reason's boasted anodyne defies , "
the uneasy mind , " Penned in the prison of this mortal mould
